V. 87. When you have got the province that you look for, put reins upon your temper and desires ; pity the poor natives; the princes you will see have all the marrow sucked from out their bones. Think of the lawS, the trust committed 10 you, the honours that await the good, the fate of those who were condemned for robbing the Cilicians. Go, get an anctioneer to sell your clothes, Chaerippus, and straight say nothing; it were mere maduess to throw away your fare besides.
